# Acme Loan Tracker â€“ MongoDB Prototype

This project implements a document-based system to manage and track special loan applications for Acme Financial Corp using MongoDB.

It fulfills the enhanced requirements including:
- Application submission
- Status updates (received, processing, accepted, rejected)
- Note tracking across subphases
- Recording rejection reasons and loan terms

---

## Getting Started in GitHub Codespace

Follow the steps below to install MongoDB, start the service, and run the test script inside your Codespace environment.

---

### Install MongoDB

Open the terminal and run:

```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y mongodb
